it.polimi.deib.p2pchat.discovery

Class DeviceTabList

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.deib.p2pchat.discovery.DeviceTabList

  • public class DeviceTabList
extends java.lang.Object
    Class that represent the tab's list of WiFiChatFragment This class contains a logic to "remap" the tab index to the List of WifiP2pDevice index. Because the first tab is reserved to WiFiP2pServicesFragment.

    Created by Stefano Cappa on 12/02/15.

      • getDevice

        public WifiP2pDevice getDevice(int pos)
        Method to get a WifiP2pDevice specifying the position of the element in the list. If the condition pos>=0 && pos <= deviceList.size() - 1 is false, return null.
        Parameters:
        pos - integer position
        Returns:
        WifiP2pDevice element at position pos, inside the deviceList or null.

      • setDevice

        public void setDevice(int pos,
                      WifiP2pDevice device)
        Method that sets a WifiP2pDevice at position pos inside the deviceList. This method replaces the element at position pos, if this deviceList.size() have an element at this position. If not, the device will be added to the deviceList, at position pos. This method never fails! You have the warranty that the element will be added to the list. If you pass a device==null, in the list you will get a null element. Be careful!
        Parameters:
        pos - integer position
        device - WifiP2pDevice element the you want add to the deviceList.

      • addDeviceIfRequired

        public void addDeviceIfRequired(WifiP2pDevice device)
        Method to add a WifiP2pDevice in the list, only if it isn't already in. If the list contains null elements, this method search the first one and it replaces with the device parameter. If all the element in the list are !=null, it adds the new device ad the end.

        This method never fails! You have the warranty that the element will be added to the list. If you pass a device==null, in the list you will get a null element. Be careful!
        Parameters:
        device - WifiP2pDevice element the you want add to the deviceList.

      • containsElement

        public boolean containsElement(WifiP2pDevice device)
        Method that check if a WifiP2pDevice is in the deviceList. If the device parameter is null, this method returns false!
        Parameters:
        device - WifiP2pDevice element.
        Returns:
        true if the element is in the list, false otherwise or if the device parameter is null.

      • indexOfElement

        public int indexOfElement(WifiP2pDevice device)
        Method to get the index position of a WifiP2pDevice from deviceList. If the device is not contained in the list or device == null, it returns -1.

        Attention: sometimes Android gives a WifiP2pDevice without the deviceName. For this reason i check the element in the list only with the deviceAddress.
        Parameters:
        device - WifiP2pDevice element.
        Returns:
        int that represents the index inside the List deviceList.

        Method to retrieve the size of deviceList
        Returns:
        int that represents the number of elements in deviceList
